adjectives.description: moorish (comparative more moorish, superlative most moorish)

entries.meaning: (now rare) Of ground, soil etc: boggy, marshy. [from 15th c.]
examples: [G]low-worms, fire-drakes, meteors, ignis fatuus  […]  with many such that appear in moorish grounds, about churchyards, moist valleys, or where battles have been fought  […] .

entries.meaning: Resembling or characteristic of a moor; abounding in moorland. [from 16th c.]
examples: He recommended to me to plant a considerable part of a large moorish farm which I had purchased, and he made several calculations of the expence and profit: for he delighted in exercising his mind on the science of numbers.
